3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with feature extraction and classification, which are important tasks in AI. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses the rectified linear unit (ReLU) activation function, which is commonly used in neural networks. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with image and video processing, which are important areas in multimedia research.
